!!!
%html
  %head
    %title Ruby Holidays Gem
  %body
  
    %h1= "What Holidays Are Happening #{@when}?"
    
    - if @holidays.length > 0
      %ul
        - @holidays.each do |h|
          %li
            = h[:name]
            in
            = h[:regions]
    - else
      %strong None (that we know of).  How sad.

    %form{:method => 'get'}
      %label Try another date? Type it and hit Enter.
      %br
      %input{:type => 'date', :name => 'date'}
      
  %p
    %small
      What is this?  A super slim interface on the 
      %a{:href => 'https://github.com/alexdunae/holidays'} Ruby Holidays gem.
      Can you make it prettier?
      %a{:href => 'https://github.com/alexdunae/holidays-www'} Grab the code and make it better.